  "text": "Bifidobacteria are members of the, one of the main microbial taxa of the human gut microbiota. Their abundance varies depending on age, being one of the most prevalent microorganisms in newborns and infants. In addition, members of the species Bifidobacterium longum, Bifidobacterium breve, Bifidobacterium bifidum and Bifidobacterium animalis have been used as probiotics due to the scientific evidence of specific beneficial effects on the human host [CITATION_1] .",
